# Microsoft Confirms Windows Security Update Breaks VPN Connections

Updated December 19 with news of two further Microsoft Windows update failures, one security-related and the other not, in addition to the previously reported one impacting VPN connections, this time affecting RemoteApp connection failures, preventing the streaming of Windows applications from the cloud for Azure Virtual Desktop users, as well as another, an extended security update for Windows 10, that managed to break message queuing.
Updating your operating system has never been more vital, given the number of critical security vulnerabilities being fixed across iOS, macOS, and, of course, Windows right now. The very last thing anyone needs to read is a confirmation from Microsoft that yet another Windows security update has broken stuff. This time, it is VPN access for a certain subset of users. Hereâ€™s what you need to know about the connectivity issues facing those users of third-party VPN apps.
